<DocsLayout title={title}>
<h1>Documentation</h1>
<p>
progrok documents one operating model: activate your xAI OAuth session once,
then use that session through a local OpenAI-compatible proxy and direct Grok
tool commands. The docs are organized around that bridge, not around API keys.
</p>

<div class="callout strong">
  <strong>Read this first</strong>
  <p>
    If you are evaluating progrok, start with the OAuth bridge page. It explains
    why Hermes Agent, OpenClaw, Grok Build-style workflows, and progrok all care
    about the same OAuth session pattern.
  </p>
</div>

